Details (or descriptions) are longer sentences that explain what you do.
Unique Features are very short, punchy phrases that stack on top of your existing ad text.
Think of Unique Features as quick "bonus reasons" to choose you. They should not repeat entire sentences from your descriptions. Instead, they should call out standout perks.', 'How are Unique Features different from Headlines and Details?

Headlines are the main clickable blue text in your ad.
Details (or descriptions) are longer sentences that explain what you do.
Unique Features are very short, punchy phrases that stack on top of your existing ad text.
